OL,3,CHigher than expected jump in inflation
OL,4,Cto 3% may not be as bad as it looks
OL,6,FThe jump in Consumer Prices Index
OL,7,F(CPI) inflation to 3% has taken
OL,8,Fanalysts a little by surprise (it was
OL,9,Fexpected to hit 2.8%). But it may not
OL,10,Fbe quite as bad as it looks.
OL,12,FThe rise in food and non-alcoholic
OL,13,Fdrink inflation to 3.3% is definitely
OL,14,Fconcerning because it hits the poorest
OL,15,Fhouseholds the hardest.
OL,17,FBut the other two big drivers of this
OL,18,Fjump are unlikely to have the same
OL,19,Feffect next month.
