OL,3,CHigher than expected jump in inflation
OL,4,Cto 3% may not be as bad as it looks
OL,6,FOne is airfares - usually those take-
OL,7,Foff dramatically in December and then
OL,8,Fplunge back down again in January.
OL,10,FBut for technical reasons the price
OL,11,Fincrease in December 2024 was nowhere
OL,12,Fnear as pronounced as usual and so the
OL,13,Fsubsequent drop in January 2025 was
OL,14,Falso smaller.
OL,16,FAnother major driver was the VAT which
OL,17,Fthe government slapped on private
OL,18,Fschool fees from January. That pushed
OL,19,Fthose up by a hefty 13%.
