OL,3,CHigher than expected jump in inflation
OL,4,Cto 3% may not be as bad as it looks
OL,6,FAlthough some of that effect might
OL,7,Fstill be felt next month (depending on
OL,8,Fwhen the bills go through), it is
OL,9,Fgenerally considered a one-off effect
OL,10,Fas a result of a policy decision and
OL,11,Ftherefore not integral to the overall
OL,12,Finflationary picture.
OL,14,FThis pair of unusual features -
OL,15,Fairfares and school fees - means the
OL,16,FBank of England may be less likely to
OL,17,Fhold interest rates higher for longer
OL,18,Fas a result of Wednesday's CPI.
