OL,3,CHigher than expected jump in inflation
OL,4,Cto 3% may not be as bad as it looks
OL,6,FBut let's not get too excited;
OL,7,Finflation is still expected to rise
OL,8,Fthis year (to 3.7% thinks the Bank),
OL,9,Fgrowth is still poor to non-existent
OL,10,Fand we have yet to feel the full
OL,11,Feffects of the chancellor's hike to
OL,12,Femployer national insurance.
OL,14,FSo even if it's not as bad as it looks
OL,15,Ftoday, it's still pretty bad.
